      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even if the brake pads still have life in them, other components can still cause the high-pitched squealing noise. Possibly, dirt or debris can accumulate in the brake caliper, brake master cylinder, or brake hoses, causing friction and the squealing sound. Check the brake hoses and caliper for any blockages or leaks, and also inspect the brake master cylinder for any moisture or issues. Cleaning the brake caliper and hoses with compressed air can sometimes resolve the issue.",
